{
  "text": "Like P. falciparum, P. knowlesi can invade erythrocytes in every stage of life, not only very young ones as P. vivax and P. ovale or old erythrocytes as P. malariae [CITATION_1] . As the intra-erythrocytic cycle is only 24 hr, P. knowlesi may cause rapid clinical deterioration, and in almost 7% of cases it has a severe, lifetreating course with multiorgan failure (as in falciparum malaria) [CITATION_2] . Studies demonstrate seasonal variations of all Plasmodium species, with maximum notifications for P. knowlesi occurring in June [CITATION_3] . According to some studies, one infective bite is probably adequate to infect a monkey, while human studies have shown that volunteers exposed to 2 bites of infected mosquitoes do not always become infected [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "1373889",
